module.exports = "\r\n<style>\r\n    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Fira+Sans+Extra+Condensed:600&display=swap');\r\n</style>\r\n  \r\n<div class=\"container text-center pt-5 pb-5\">\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-12\">\r\n            <div class=\"h3 display-4 text-uppercase font-weight-bold pt-3\">Appreciations</div>\r\n          </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-12\">\r\n              <div class=\"h3  text-uppercase text-center pt-5\">Faculty Speak</div>\r\n                  <ngx-slick-carousel class=\"carousel\" \r\n                  #slickModal=\"slick-carousel\" \r\n                  [config]=\"slideConfig\" \r\n                  (init)=\"slickInit($event)\"\r\n                  (breakpoint)=\"breakpoint($event)\"\r\n                  (afterChange)=\"afterChange($event)\"\r\n                  (beforeChange)=\"beforeChange($event)\">\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe1\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe2\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe3\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe4\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n                  <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe5\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n                </div>\r\n                </ngx-slick-carousel>\r\n              <br>\r\n          \r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n          <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n            <div class=\"text-justify textarea card-text pr-2\" style=\"width:100%; height:500px ;border:none;overflow:scroll;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:scroll; font-size: 1em\">\r\n              <div>         \r\n                          <div class=\"h5\">Patricia Veronica Ingels, Senior School Psychology</div>\r\n                          Inventure Academy presented an environment for me to learn as I taught for the first time, and for me to grow as a teacher while I watched my students grow. The supportive culture nurtures creativity in the classroom, where learning opportunities are in abundance, for both the learners and the teacher. \r\n                          The learners are at the centre of the lesson, where they are encouraged to believe that their voices matter, that every mistake is a learning opportunity and every challenge is to be submitted. Just as I was mentored to believe by senior faculty members.\r\n                          <br><br>\r\n                          <div class=\"h5\">Aparajita Dutta, Senior School History</div>\r\n                          A happy place, a sunny place. Where students enjoy learning, where teachers and students forge 'forever bonds', where students feel more at home, than their homes! Inventure believes in instilling a sense of pride and connect among its students and staff, who willingly uphold and display the ethos of the school. \r\n                          I have been associated with Inventure for the past one year - both as a parent and a teacher, and I can vouch for the wonderful, warm and nurturing environment in which children grow up here, with equal focus on academics and beyond academics. Students are given opportunities to explore their potential and hone their talents, help them prepare for their future and more importantly become socially responsible citizens. \r\n                          I am really glad that I am part of Inventure!\r\n                          <br><br>\r\n                          <div class=\"h5\">Mona Dhawan, Kindergarten Coordinator</div>\r\n                          It has been an extremely enriching experience at Inventure Academy. Becoming part of a dynamic team of energized and highly competent teachers has helped in expanding the personal and professional sides of my life.\r\n                          I have been with Inventure for four years- both as a parent and a teacher. My time in school has developed my philosophy of valuing each child as an individual as well as working towards making them socially responsible citizens.  Inventure is a vibrant place that gives children many opportunities and experiences in order to engage, motivate, and prepare them for the future.\r\n                          I am proud to be a part of Inventure!!\r\n                          <br><br>\r\n                          <div class=\"h5\">Namrata Bhandari, Kindergarten Educator</div>   \r\n                          Being a teacher at Inventure is a different experience from anything I have ever experienced. It is an impressive organization that makes educators feel supported and equipped in their efforts to change lives. The Inventure community strives to create an environment that makes learning meaningful in a student-centered environment.\r\n                          At Inventure we believe that learners are the main participants in the class, the ones who discover knowledge, while the teachers channel their efforts in the right direction. \r\n                          I have enjoyed teaching my students as well as learning from them.  I believe every day is a new opportunity to learn and my main goal is to prepare my students to be successful in the rest of their school years and to be life-long learners.”\r\n                          Inventure is a wonderful community of teachers and learners.\r\n\r\n                  </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-12\">\r\n          <div class=\"h3  text-uppercase text-center pt-5\">Parent Speak</div>\r\n              <ngx-slick-carousel class=\"carousel\" \r\n              #slickModal=\"slick-carousel\" \r\n              [config]=\"slideConfig\" \r\n              (init)=\"slickInit($event)\"\r\n              (breakpoint)=\"breakpoint($event)\"\r\n              (afterChange)=\"afterChange($event)\"\r\n              (beforeChange)=\"beforeChange($event)\">\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe6\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe7\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe8\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe9\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe10\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe11\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe12\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe13\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe14\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe15\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe16\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe17\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe18\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe19\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </ngx-slick-carousel>\r\n          <br>\r\n      \r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n          <div class=\"text-justify textarea card-text pr-2\" style=\"width:100%; height:500px ;border:none;overflow:scroll;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:scroll; font-size: 1em\">\r\n            <div>         \r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Amit Gupta, parent of Divij Gupta</div>\r\n                         We are humbled by Divij's early successes and feel blessed that he is being rewarded for his diligence matched with his intelligence in this competitive environment where many other bright students don't get such a chance and get discovered.  As parents, our only contribution is to enable his aspirations and gently nudge him to be more rounded and always be grounded. We are also very thankful to Inventure Academy for providing such a conducive environment towards Divij's holistic development. An institution providing measured freedom, avenues and the right atmosphere has a very significant role in what our \"next Gen\" achieves. I can only share with the parent fraternity that this generation needs to be encouraged and be engaged in a variety of things especially sports, fitness and others besides Education to discover their passion while having superior outcomes in their chosen areas. Divij's exposure to drumming and sports (running) immensely helped him in what he is achieving and accentuating his passion. \r\n                         <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\"> Swati Kerkar, Parent of Omkar Kerkar</div>\r\n                          Our son Omkar has made us and his school, Inventure Academy, immensely proud. We are feeling extremely happy for him. This is entirely his own dedication, determination and hard work all the way. This accomplishment is indeed going to boost his confidence and motivation. Omkar has shown dedicated passion towards Mathematics right from his toddler years and his interest towards this subject has grown taller with him. Along with the various opportunities available at Inventure Academy that he happily avails, Omkar also enjoys playing sports like chess, badminton and frisbee. Playing the piano in the senior school band has groomed and positively shaped his personality. We would like to thank all his teachers whose support and guidance nurtured him well throughout his student life. We truly appreciate all of the school’s efforts.  Thank you from the bottom of our hearts for convincing us to join Inventure last year.\r\n                          <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\"> Shashank Jain, parent of Abhishek Jain</div>\r\n                        A real proud moment for us. It’s hard to hit that level in one subject, twice in a row, to do it in two and as diverse as Arts and Science is incredible. Not sure we can take any credit for that, other than the fact that we put him in Inventure. It’s been his teachers and the school that allowed him the flexibility to go that wide, mentored him and most importantly challenged him to put in that last ounce.  \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\"> Deepak Kandwal, parent of Inika Kandwal</div>   \r\n                        Like every other achievement, a major part of the credit for this achievement goes to the environment provided by Inventure Academy. We remain indebted to the management and the academic team of Inventure for creating an environment that inculcates excellence in every sense of the word.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Alok & Shefali Kuchlous, parents of Sahil</div>\r\n                        We are very thankful to the teachers at Inventure for the constant encouragement and\r\n                        guidance that they provided to all the children. The school also encouraged Sahil to continue\r\n                        participating in extra-curricular activities ensuring that he developed not only academically but\r\n                        more holistically.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Simi Ballani, Associate Director, Preschool: 'Little Millennium’, parent of Sera</div>\r\n                        I take the pleasure of writing this mail to thank the Kindergarten team of Inventure for hosting a wonderful and memorable event! Every parent would agree with me when I say that this school not only gives education but also enhances the ethical values in the child and most importantly teaches them to be happy!\r\n                        It’s a proud moment for parents when they love to say that their child is a part of such a wonderful place of learning. Thank you for a great show and giving us a great learning through such events. The 'theme' was extremely creative... the message was the need of the time. Our daughter and all children performed very well! I wish to appreciate your team ....each and every one and in particular Ms. Shanthala! We can proudly say...  our decision was right in choosing your school for our daughter Sera!\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Gopal Pingali, parent of Sahithi,  Lalitha and Sreekari</div>\r\n                        The fundamental philosophy of this school is Multiple Intelligences and bringing up well rounded children and we can see that since we have 3 children going to school here, we feel that very personally. Each one is very unique, each one is very brilliant and outstanding in her own way and I think the school brings that out and they have the confidence. With Sahithi the other two have certainly been inspired but how they channelize it is very different. Lalitha has also gone to the science fair. She is doing things and representing India this year as one of 2 middle school students which is great. She got inspired by her sister but she is also very very different in terms of the way she goes about art or music. I’m glad she is able to find her own avenues at Inventure.\r\n                        And the 3rd one Sreekari is completely different. She is very social, really enjoys being with people, she can connect with any age group and she also is finding ways to get inspired and excel. I am seeing that the school is really bringing out the whole notion that each child is unique and each child can excel in their own way.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Aruna Pingali, parent of Sahithi,  Lalitha and Sreekari</div>\r\n                        The students in Inventure welcome and respect the differences in each other and they have the confidence that whatever merits or interest they have within them, their personality, they can do their best. That is, I think, more important in the overall development of the child than pure academics. I would like to thank the school for everything they have done not only for Sahithi but for every child in the school. The school has been growing over the years and I am really proud of the way the facilities are being arranged and expanding. And as the school is expanding they are narrowing down and zeroing in on the most important values the school is based upon and that is truly wonderful. So thank you so much for giving our kids the opportunity to become what they are and I’m looking forward to seeing more great stars come out of the academic institute.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Puneet Singh, parent of Kunal and Sachin</div>\r\n                        My two boys - Kunal who is in 10th Grade and Sachin who is in 8th are a bit different;  as in Kunal is very much into the sciences of things, computers and maths. He wanted to make robotic stuff so we came to the school and said, ‘Hey, look there are some robotics competitions out there and Kunal wants to participate;  and in fact, there are a bunch of kids in his grade who want to participate.’ The school was very supportive. It provided the platform, the space in the school. Aaron came along and became a mentor. So 10 kids went and participated in FLL (First Lego League) and later in World Robot Olympiad (WRO). Now I see that its become a culture and many kids do it over the years and I think those are positive things in the school.\r\n                        The younger one is different. Right from childhood, he was into reading, writing and communication aspects, drama and other things. He actually wanted to become an author.  So we went to the school saying he wants to pursue this. He actually published his first book a couple of years ago and wrote his second one recently! The school has been very supportive and enabling.  I’m not claiming that the school has all the solutions figured out but the fact that his strengths are different, his interests are different, they at least go out and try and find how can they help and let the kids fly. I am happy, the kids are happy here, what else would a parent want!\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Ritu and Ashutosh Wakankar, parents of Kabir and Aman</div>\r\n                        We are writing this to convey our heartfelt thank you and warmest wishes for all of you at Inventure Academy.  Some of you may know that we are relocating to the US in June and hence Kabir Wakankar and Aman Wakankar will not be continuing their sessions at Inventure from 2018 onwards.\r\n                        Teachers and mentors like you are what our children needed during their formative years and you offered more than that. The Inventuring week, Outbound trips, FLL, PBL, Production day and many such things is what Kabir and Aman will cherish for the rest of their lives.\r\n                        Please treat this as our letter of gratitude and thanks for all that you have done for our children in the last 2 years which I believe were the most important years in their student life. That's the magic of Inventure and I am glad we got to experience that first-hand. \r\n                        Wish you all the very best in both personal and professional lives. Please pass it on to other teachers and Nooraine Ma'am, who i have missed as i didn't have their email id's.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Lakshmipraba Sankaran parent of Adhiseshan Raghavendran</div>\r\n                        It’s been a year since the 4 trees from Sarjapur were transplanted. 3 peepal and 1 neem out of which Inventure has adopted 3 trees (2 peepal and 1 neem). This citizen driven activity has inspired many more citizens from all over India to consider transplantation as an option. These trees are indeed a moment of pride always for Inventure.\r\n                        Gives immense pleasure to see the peepal trees surviving beautifully under love, care and great positivity at Inventure. My heartfelt appreciation to Nooraine for being broad minded to adopt the trees. My heartfelt appreciation for the patience shown by Varsha and Lawrence to support with the various interactions in this 1 year for the tree care. My heartfelt and sincere appreciation for the gardeners for the love and care shown towards the tree care.\r\n                        It gives immense pleasure for me to see the positive learning that the kids would get knowing about this activity that trees have to be nurtured and how important they are to bring in rains. It was a great learning and bonding for me towards tree care and I feel happy that my son is in a school environment which nurtures this feeling.\r\n                        Soon I will be sharing the tree transplantation video (got slightly delayed due to editing by the producers) with the school for sharing with the kids, faculty, staff and parents.\r\n                        \r\n\r\n                        ...realised that most of his strengths derive from the foundations laid by Inventure. From the way that he was taught history, to the knowledge gained by Our Safety Our Voice; from confidence gained as part of the Student Council to exposure from hours spent at Samarthanam. \r\n                        Parveen Sikand, mother of Vir & Avanti\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Tanya Bali, Varun and Tia</div>\r\n                        I write to applaud the tremendous effort that has been going into the various aspects of coordination of so many activities that are currently happening in school. Truly amazing and have a complete “wow” element attached.  I simply love the google forms.\r\n                        Kudos to the entire team and all good wishes for the production event. We look forward to being there and witnessing yet another superlative performance.\r\n                        Proud to be part of the Inventure Family.\r\n                        \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Anjana Perumal parent of Aarya</div>\r\n                        Heard raving reviews from some of the kids from other schools who attended Model Parliament - 2017, on how well behaved, hospitable and polite the Inventure kids were to the guest. Coming from kids of similar age group must mean a lot. They truly enjoyed the experience and the food !! Well done \r\n                        \r\n\r\n                        I think learning has to be fun - because that’s when you internalize it, synthesize it and that’s when it’s part of your toolkit when you are growing up and you can actually call back on all these learnings; to be a better person, contributing citizen to society and I think that’s very important.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Parent in COL video</div>\r\n                        I see the passion with the kids. The depth that they are building in terms of acquiring knowledge. Broad topics covered across authors, writers; food preparation, adulteration, traffic conditions and how to improve them so kids are gaining a wider perspective and I am thrilled to be part of what is truly a Celebration of Learning!\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Anuja Venkataraman, parent of Varun</div>\r\n                        To the teachers, co-ordinators and school head of Inventure, I would like to appreciate the ideas you brought to the Inventuring week this past week. The ecoedu nature walk, the pet dog interaction session, the marking parking lot project - these were all experiences my son spoke about. Talking about the nature walk he said he didn't know Inventure had so much! (variety of plants) \r\n                        My son Varun tremendously enjoyed the choice time, theater, though he was quite unsure of how it would turn out before it started. He was extremely appreciative of Prateek Sir, who apparently has even worked with Amitabh Bachchan! \r\n                        His experience with the theater choice time has led me to share my joy and thank you for the efforts to bring a variety of high quality exposure to the children. \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Mayur Murthy, parent of Arya</div>\r\n                        As part of Team Inventure, my son's experience of being a MUN Delegate and going on to win the Best Delegate and the Best Delegation awards at WEMUN China, 2018 has been priceless. Competing at an international conference and winning accolades gives every one of these Inventure kids such immense self-confidence in their ability and helps to reinforce their belief that they can compete with any of their peers from around the world. In addition, the sheer knowledge gained from researching the issue at hand and their exposure to people and places from another culture is more than they could ever learn in a classroom setting.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Sejal and Priyesh Mody, parents of Anirudh</div>\r\n                        Inventure Academy truly upholds its motto in preparing our children for life and has a platform for every child. Mentoring them for experiences such as Model UN provides the perfect broad based platform for children to build solid researching capabilities, interact on a global level and experience the much needed \"out of comfort zone\" environment! Wish we had had these opportunities when we were kids!\r\n                        \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Tripta & Taranjeet Singh Rekhi, parents of Teghveer</div>\r\n                        It gives us immense pride that Teghveer has topped IGCSE Math worldwide in 2018. Mathematics is his favourite subject. He had put in a lot of effort and we are happy that he did well. Teghveer is also passionate about basketball and drums. He could study well along with pursuing his interests in sports and music due to the support from his school. We are grateful to the teachers and Inventure Academy for creating the environment that helped him perform well.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Mr Madan, parent of Kabir</div>\r\n                        Kabir worked very hard for this. I am happy to see that he found Sociology meaningful and engaging. His teachers across his subjects were a source of stimulation, encouragement and inspiration. Our grateful thanks to them.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        \r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">The Kandwals, parents of Inika</div>\r\n                        Inika is the first one in the family to take up geography as a subject at AS level (senior secondary). That decision meant that there would be no help available to her at home for geography, unlike other subjects like maths, physics, chemistry and biology.\r\n                        The large part of credit for Inika's performance in geography goes to faculty members at Inventure. It starts with inculcating the interest for the geography at very young age, to giving the confidence and courage to take the independent decision and to guide her to the level of national best performance in geography.”\r\n                        \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">The Jains, Abhishek’s parents</div>\r\n                        It is a proud moment, we live to see days like this. Even though Abhi put in the handwork and the diligence, his Computer Science teacher, and Inventure should get the credit in greater measure. Abhi has been in Inventure since 3rd grade, and the school’s philosophy of letting the kids explore what they want really want to do and then providing the environment to execute has been that x-factor that you need for such an outcome. We hope he can continue to make his teachers and school proud as he continues his journey further.\r\n                        \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Ms Rao, parent of Maya Patra</div>\r\n                        Coming from ICSE, Maya did badly in her AS levels in English Literature, but she picked herself up and worked very hard to get an A* in  A levels.  Her teacher Ms Sowmya Ramesh was very supportive and helped her get back on track. Her other teachers and the school also gave her a lot of help and encouragement. We are proud of her fighting spirit.\r\n                        \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Tanya Eldred Bhat, parent of Mia</div>\r\n                        Many congratulations on a wonderful completion of this module of PBL on Waste Management. As a parent it was a wonderful experience for me to sit through the 45 minutes slotted for this. Time flew by as we were all so involved and engrossed in the proceedings. Your personal passion for both subjects reflected through and certainly injected the students with a similar enthusiasm. The thoroughness of the entire project, the answering of the most important “WHY” and the learning that has happened, both in the subject math, as well as a real life problem like Waste Management is exemplary.\r\n                        It was heartening to know that the students of grade 5 worked on a similar PBL on water conservation. Such real world topics are of huge significance in our lives today and it’s never too early to sensitise children. I do believe that when we bring a change in children, it changes the world of tomorrow. Children are the greatest ripples of change. \r\n                        Thank you very much for a wonderful session. And for all the hard work you put in to facilitate learning to happen. \r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                        <div class=\"h5\">Suparna Shantagiri, parent of Shivjeet and Surabhi</div>\r\n                        My son, Shivjeet Parthasarathy, currently in Grade 11 AS, was a product of the traditional Indian schooling system till the 7th Grade. In the typical “convent school”, discipline is of paramount importance with classes being rigidly taught, emphasis on fixed question and answers to be reproduced by rote, no discussions etc. Being more of a free flowing and imaginative thinker, Shivjeet was miserable in this set-up.  We looked at alternate streams of schooling. The schools which adopted a more interactive style of teaching were a little too relaxed in their overall approach. A progressive style of teaching meant that the school system too was quite unstructured, the approach to life itself was different. Especially in matters like discipline, academic rigor, good manners- old fashioned values which mattered to old school parents like us. We were looking for a school which made learning a voyage of discovery, encouraged and expanded the child’s mind, helping him reach his full potential. With a right mix of strictness and regulation, so that he learns to be a striving and responsible member of society. Inventure Academy’s biggest success has been in getting this formula right, unlike most other schools.\r\n                        Inventure Academy proved a turning point for Shivjeet. Academically, it has been wonderful for him. He enjoys his classes, the discussions and debates. While classes are enjoyable, there is strong academic rigor. From a point of failing in almost every subject before coming here, he secured 2 A*s, 5 As and 2 Bs in the IGCSE exams. He jumped into every opportunity offered by Inventure to explore every talent in a child, be it Tournament of Minds (for the performing arts), Sports (of every kind), Model United Nations,  Community Outreach Programmes, Our Lakes Our Voice, Changemaker….. the list is endless. He has become a good public speaker winning awards at MUNs, Tournament of Minds, acted in the school production, won medals for his house at the Swimming Meet.  Each of these activities have helped him develop different aspects to his personality. Inventure believes that every child should form an all-round personality – excelling  in at least one sport and one extra curricular activity. While most schools just pay slip service to this concept, Inventure actually implements it. We can see the result in our son – he has grown into a confident and responsible young man who will surely be a success and an asset to society.\r\n                        Naturally, we made sure our daughter, Surabhi, entered Inventure from Grade 1 itself. The teaching methodology employed – Theme-based learning and Reading & Writing Programme really give the child a headstart in life. More than just teaching facts and concepts, it is all about inculcating a thought process in the child. The child is trained to observe, analyse and reflect on her environment; taught how to organize and structure her thoughts, how to present and communicate them effectively. To break down a problem/situation into various elements, to analyse each one and finally put it all back together for a solution/opinion. Through continuous discussions and writing, the child develops strong presentation abilities – both written and oral.  All important skills needed to make a success of adult life. By the end of Grade3, we can see these traits developing very strongly in Surabhi.\r\n                        The sporting culture is very strong in Inventure. This of course is evident in the successes of Inventure students in various sports at interschool, club, state and national levels. To encourage the child, all successes are celebrated at the school assembly as well as in social media. What is more heartening is that all children are taught every sport, athletics, football, basketball, cricket, TT, swimming…. They come to enjoy it, regardless of how good they are at it. All coaches are extremely encouraging. Every child who does not make it to the house or school team is made to feel that he can become a good player and will be given an opportunity the next time.\r\n                        The Music, Dance, Arts, PODs classes teach every child the basics of, and give an understanding and appreciation of each of the performing arts. I once found Surabhi explaining in great detail, to her friend who learns the piano, the differences between the Western Octave and the Saptaswaras of Carnatic music.  The Tournament of Minds and School Production gives each child an opportunity to showcase his/her skills. By the time the child leaves school, she is bound to be a well-rounded and enriched personality.\r\n                        College Guidance and Career Counselling is another much appreciated feature. It is hard for parents to keep up with the latest trends and career opportunities. The college visits and talks, information about careers, advice on various exams all help the child and parents take decisions on the future path to take. The impressive list of college placements every year is testament to this.\r\n                        Community Outreach and Changemaker Programmes are another unique feature at Inventure. They instill a strong sense of social responsibility and belonging in the child. Our children lead very privileged lives and end up being insulated from the real India. Such programmes help sensitise them to the disadvantaged and develop a wanting to give back.\r\n                        Having a wide range of extra-curricular programmes has had an interesting side effect, in my opinion. There is a large youth presence across various departments (like Music, Dance, Arts, Changemaker etc). Students of high school do not view these teachers as “teachers” but more as “friends”, closer to them in mental age. They discuss music, games, world affairs, with them - anything under the sun. They are seen as a “bridge generation” between the students and teachers (the same as parents), and therefore worth listening to. I believe that this kind of grown-up interaction is a great psychological benefit to teenagers before they enter adulthood themselves. It exposes them to a variety of opinions, helps them form their own views, build strong friendships across age groups and is great practice for adult life. Along with his mentor, it gives the child a number of people he can turn to, for issues he cannot discuss with his parents.\r\n                        Mentorship is another great  programme at Inventure. The child feels there is somebody looking out for him at all times in the school, a guide and advisor.\r\n                        All in all, Inventure Academy definitely was the right choice of school and we heartily recommend it to every parent.\r\n                        <br><br>\r\n                </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-12\">\r\n          <div class=\"h3  text-uppercase text-center pt-5\">Alumni Speak</div>\r\n              <ngx-slick-carousel class=\"carousel\" \r\n              #slickModal=\"slick-carousel\" \r\n              [config]=\"slideConfig\" \r\n              (init)=\"slickInit($event)\"\r\n              (breakpoint)=\"breakpoint($event)\"\r\n              (afterChange)=\"afterChange($event)\"\r\n              (beforeChange)=\"beforeChange($event)\">\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe1\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe2\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe3\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe4\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe5\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </ngx-slick-carousel>\r\n          <br>\r\n      \r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n      <div class=\"text-justify textarea card-text pr-2\" style=\"width:100%; height:500px ;border:none;overflow:scroll;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:scroll; font-size: 1em\">\r\n        <div>         \r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Divij Gupta  Grade 12,  batch of 2020</div>\r\n                    “It is a surreal feeling to get three ‘Top of the World’ ranks. It reaffirms my interest in Math and motivates me to work harder in the same stream going forward. I am grateful to my teachers, my school and my parents for their continuous support.” <br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Omkar Kerkar Grade 12,  batch of 2020</div>\r\n                    “I was extremely happy to have been this successful and would not have been able to achieve this without the help of my teachers who have always ensured that I was always positively challenged. The very strong and friendly competition in my class also urged me to do better.”<br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\"> Shashank Jain, parent of Abhishek Jain</div>\r\n                    A real proud moment for us. It’s hard to hit that level in one subject, twice in a row, to do it in two and as diverse as Arts and Science is incredible. Not sure we can take any credit for that, other than the fact that we put him in Inventure. It’s been his teachers and the school that allowed him the flexibility to go that wide, mentored him and most importantly challenged him to put in that last ounce.  \r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Abhishek Jain, batch of 2018-19,  received the High Achievement Award in AS Level Computer Science </div>   \r\n                    “Feeling really good right now! Definitely one of my proudest moments. I'm really passionate about both subjects and am pursuing these fields now at university, so it's really great to see that reflect in the results I've been able to achieve. There was no way I could have done this without Gousia Ma'am or Aaron Sir. Both put in so much work in order to help me succeed, and were there every step along the way. I'd also like to thank the school for the entire support system. I had a couple of really hard decisions to make during the first term exams, and the school really pulled through in helping me keep everything together. Lastly, I thank my parents for just being there, they've been my biggest supporters from day 1. Once again, feeling really good! Will try to continue this trend, and keep at it.”\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Inika Kandwal, batch of 2019, received the High Achievement Award in AS Level Geography</div>\r\n                    “I couldn't have done this without my teachers and am incredibly indebted to them. Inventure’s flexibility also allowed me to pursue the number and kind of subjects I wanted at the AS and A Levels to achieve what I have. I think what made the difference was Inventure's learning environment. Before coming to Inventure, I had previously never learned to understand but learned to memorize. The AS and A-level course, specifically, allowed learning beyond the pages of my textbook and enabled me to undertake situations around the world as my focus of study in Geography. My learning experience would be incomplete without the role of my Geography teacher- Shubhra Sinha. She not only taught me what I know but also pushed me to do better. She has mentored me throughout the years and not only supported me in her subject but also my high school experience in its entirety. \r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Samyuktha Srivatsa\r\n                      Grade 12, batch of 2019\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      I'm quite happy with the marks I have received. I owe my success entirely to the teachers I was fortunate to have at Inventure,  who taught me with so much passion and interest, and went out of their way to support me. The Inventure culture helped me find and hone new avenues of interest that I'm very excited to take further.  I continue to pursue my interests out of the classroom -whether classical dance and music or coding, debate and social entrepreneurship. I am lucky to have parents and a sister who encourage me.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Ritu Alapat, Grade 12, batch of 2019</div>\r\n                    I am extremely grateful to God and to my teachers at Inventure Academy for consistently helping me these past two years. They have always been there to clear any doubts I've had, and have guided me throughout my time at Inventure. I wouldn't have been able to achieve much without them, and will carry the lessons they've taught me throughout life. \r\n                    I am pleasantly surprised with my results, but also grateful that my attention in class and hard work have paid off.  Becoming a doctor and helping others has been a dream of mine for as long as I can remember, and this has shown me that it's something I can achieve if I put my mind to it. \r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Aisha Nikita Singh, Grade 12, batch of 2019</div>\r\n                    I feel so completely rewarded for all the hard work I have put in. Particularly, scoring 100 in History and Sociology was incredible. These are not just subjects that I study, but sheer passions which I thrive on! My teachers have not only given extraordinary guidance, taught me using creative methods, but have also been friends who have buoyed me up. Inventure Academy has provided me with the environment that I needed to bring out my best.\r\n                    My passion is art and design. In my spare time, I draw and paint.  In the Summer of 2015, I created several art pieces across different media and raised Rs17,500 for a brain MRI needed by a child. I have done logo design and marketing collaterals for two start-ups. I have designed two book covers for books called 'Mum' Gotta Live' and 'Chunav Sar Par Hain'.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Joel Tony Grade 10, 2018-19</div>\r\n                    I am elated on receiving my marks in the ICSE board exams. I have achieved my targets. I am very grateful to Inventure and my teachers who have supported me throughout the 10 years that I have spent at Inventure. Their constant support, motivation and exceptional teaching, has pushed me to my peak performance.\r\n                    Inventure’s vision and core values have gone a long way in shaping me as a person. Nooraine ma’am and Meenakshi ma’am always encouraged me in my endeavours. It is with their support that I have won a total of 8 national awards, out of which 5 are in academics and 3 in sports.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Dhruv Bhatia, Class of 2018; Liberal Arts, Brown University</div>\r\n                    Inventure has helped shape me into the person I am today. I have been exposed to all kinds of opportunities, ranging from music and sports, to service and teaching, allowing me to pursue what I am genuinely interested in. Inventure taught me the importance of seeing the best in people, and of the spirit of community. Most importantly, Inventure accepted me for who I am, giving me the confidence to be myself in the ‘real world’.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Anoushka Shyam, Class of 2018;  Psychology, Ashoka University</div>\r\n                    I’m so grateful for what Inventure does, not just for me but for everyone here. They are actually doing so much to change the education system; to look at each one of us as individuals with our own strengths and weaknesses and our own passions. I have had the most amazing teachers here. Every single subject I have taken I have discovered I am so passionate about and want to take it forward.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Vishwanatha Mallampooty, Class of 2018; Physics & Math, University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign</div>\r\n                    Inventure gives everyone of us the opportunity to become ourselves. For me it was through MUN, volunteering and Student Council. For others it was through music, production… Inventure needs to keep doing what it is doing and help make kids into people.\r\n                    \r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Aarushi Matiyani, Class of 2018; Debating between top 5 design schools in UK, US & India</div>\r\n                    I want to be in education. The  youth… talk about so many things  that are wrong in our country... We do our schooling in India, go abroad, and then stay there. Think it’s  hypocritical... it is our duty to come back and make a change\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Anika Desai, Class of 2018; Pursuing music</div>\r\n                    I have a huge heart... if I didn’t grow up with the people that I grew up with & was taught by the people  who taught me all these years, I wouldn't be half as nice. I look at other schools, and other people. No one has the culture and the kindness that we do, we are so open to & accepting of everyone. That’s one thing that Inventure has taught me. It’s my home, it will always be my home.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Sahithi Pingali, Class of 2018, topped the country in AS Level Biology;\r\n                      studying Environmental Engineering, Stanford University \r\n                    </div>\r\n                      Inventure gave me the flexibility I needed to balance various extracurriculars, competitions and travel, along with schoolwork. Our Lakes Our Voice inspired my lake monitoring project, and when that project took me to various competitions across the world my teachers were very understanding and supportive in helping me catch up and maintain my academics. All I want to say is a huge thank you to the amazing biology teachers I had at inventure. Zabil ma'am, who taught me all of AS and A levels; also Aditi ma'am and Radhika ma'am. They were a big part of why I love the subject and was able to learn so much\r\n                      <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Sridhar Prabhu, Class of 2016; Emmanuel College Cambridge University</div>\r\n                    Inventure really helped me find a balance in my student life. I was encouraged to pursue my interests in science as well as in sports (athletics and football). Inventure’s holistic approach in terms of the wide variety of opportunities and guidance provided really helped me realize my true potential both on and off the sports field.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Namrata Ramesh, Class of 2016; UC Berkeley: Finishing Year 2</div>\r\n                    Because Inventure takes risks, and it thinks outside of the box… It teaches you to seize opportunities, and be creative about them.  At Berkeley, you need to be more than someone who simply focuses on academics, which is what Inventure’s philosophy perfectly reflects.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Alisha Kalyanpuri Class of 2016; MBBS, JIPMER Pondicherry</div>\r\n                    Inventure was the stepping stone and breeding ground for me – in terms of everything I learned about subjects I studied, and the way I discovered myself – my passions, my inhibitions, my strengths and my hobbies. The faculty at school allowed me to go beyond what was in the textbooks and the syllabus and read around the things taught at school, which was lovely – it inculcated a passion in me for research.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Tejas Rao, Class of 2016; Honours Dual Degree Arts & Law, Gujarat National Law University</div>\r\n                    Kabir worked very hard for this. I am happy to see that he found Sociology meaningful and engaging. His teachers across his subjects were a source of stimulation, encouragement and inspiration. Our grateful thanks to them.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n                    \r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Radhika Malaviya, Class of 2014 </div>\r\n                    Inventure has always kept an eye on my passions. When I took an interest in theatre, a school production was just around the corner; when creative writing caught my fancy, a poetry competition emerged. Inventure has a way of knowing what makes each student tick. The school’s ability to nurture individuality seems ever-expanding. \r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Students -  Celebration Of Learning</div>\r\n                    ‘I think what I enjoyed most was working as a team because when you are part of something bigger than yourself you can say that you will be able to achieve a lot more.’\r\n                    ‘I learnt how to work with others and do my work more efficiently and in a better way. I have now found interest in a wide range of topics in which I had none before.’\r\n                    ‘I was able to apply my programming skills to the test and that really boosted my confidence. I am actually learning something when I do coding on my own.’\r\n                    \r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Kaavya Murugan, Head Girl Primary</div>\r\n                    I have had many learnings in my experience in the student council. One learning is to be sure of what you do because the students depend on us and we have to take our responsibility seriously. One reason I love Inventure is because it allows us to succeed in our talents.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Robin Roy, on his ICSE Board results</div>\r\n                    My teachers at Inventure and my parents have supported me all through my learning journey, encouraging me to focus on my efforts, rather than on the scores.\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Sanaya Maria Katrak, class topper with 95.75% in the ISC boards; also a Student Council member and a Changemaker Prefect. </div>\r\n                    I am thrilled with my results and credit my success to the way I was taught and supported by my teachers. My commitment and hard work has definitely paid off! \r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Anoushka Shyam, scored 94.25% in ISC; also played one of the lead roles in this year’s production - Every Inch Upstream, participated in Slam Poetry competitions and was part of a team that came in third in a National Psychology quiz.</div>\r\n                    I am very happy with my results. I am so grateful to Inventure, especially to my teachers, for pushing me to excel academically; and to the school, for providing me with many opportunities to explore my interests through extra-curricular activities.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Ananya Vepa, Grade 11</div>\r\n                    It is important to listen and understand another person’s story. We live in a very sheltered environment and the caste system really doesn’t affect us. However, it is still very prevalent in India and as privileged people we should work towards providing equal opportunities for all. Only then are we moving forward.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Shashwat Bansal, Grade 9 on Shilpa Raj’s session</div>\r\n                    Education is important and should be accessible to all. Irrespective of your socio-economic background, every individual should attempt to make a change for oneself and the community\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Arya Murthy, Grade 10, Best Delegate WEMUN Expo 2018</div>\r\n                    WEMUN was my first international MUN, and it has been an unforgettable experience. I learnt to work with people from different cultures and develop my critical thinking and negotiating skills. Everyone on the team supported each other through all the work and frustration of committee. By the end of the conference, I felt immensely proud - of my own achievement, and the incredible performance of our entire delegation. I got to meet some amazing people and open my mind to new experiences.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Kaavya Mundkur, Grade 9, Best Delegate WEMUN Expo 2018 </div>\r\n                    WEMUN taught me a lot more than just the issue in the Central African Republic, the most important being that I should not presume to know how other delegates will be until I actually meet them, as each delegate is unique! My committee focused a lot on consensus and I ended up learning how to negotiate effectively despite language and other cultural barriers.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Dhruv Iyengar, Grade 9, Best Delegate WEMUN Expo 2018</div>\r\n                    This was my first international conference and just my second MUN overall. Overall, it was one of the most amazing and best learning experiences of my life. I learnt that diplomacy extends beyond the four walls of committee to all parts of our lives. I met new people from different cultures, and faced new challenges which allowed me to tap into potential I had not previously realised.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Anjali Agarwal, Grade 12, Honourable Mention: WEMUN Expo 2018 </div>\r\n                    Attending a conference like WEMUN was an enthralling experience for me. It was my first international conference so I was able to meet people from around the globe with different perspectives and approaches to problems. There were many challenges during the conferences because of being in a different country, and I absolutely loved it! I made many new friends from China and was exposed to their different cultures and interests.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Adhir V Balaji, Grade 7, on MS Celebration of Learning 2018</div>\r\n                    We learn that failure is the key to success. We had to research again and again and do the same thing again and again, to finally get the solution.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Dhruv Bhatia, winner of the High Achievement Award in AS Level Literature in English.</div>\r\n                    My teachers at Inventure taught me in a way that not only showed me how fascinating literature is, but also that if I try hard, I can do well at anything.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n                    <div class=\"h5\">Teghveer Singh Rekhi, topped the world in IGCSE Mathematics is pursuing his AS/A Levels</div>\r\n                    I am delighted that I have topped the IGCSE Math worldwide. This would not have been possible without the support and the guidance of my teachers at Inventure Academy, parents and friends. The support from Inventure has been exceptional and brought out the best in me by encouraging and helping me balance academics and my beyond academics pursuits. A special thanks to my Math teachers for being extremely supportive of me.\r\n\r\n                    <br><br>\r\n\r\n            </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-12\">\r\n          <div class=\"h3  text-uppercase text-center pt-5\">Opinion leader Speak</div>\r\n              <ngx-slick-carousel class=\"carousel\" \r\n              #slickModal=\"slick-carousel\" \r\n              [config]=\"slideConfig\" \r\n              (init)=\"slickInit($event)\"\r\n              (breakpoint)=\"breakpoint($event)\"\r\n              (afterChange)=\"afterChange($event)\"\r\n              (beforeChange)=\"beforeChange($event)\">\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe20\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe21\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe22\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div ngxSlickItem class=\"slide\">\r\n              <iframe [src]=\"urlSafe23\" frameBorder=\"0\" width=\"100%\"></iframe>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </ngx-slick-carousel>\r\n          <br>\r\n      \r\n    </div>\r\n       \r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n"

